  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To Support Tribal Households with Food &amp; Health Support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1500 Dry Ration would be supported, 200 Individuals would be supported with reimbursement for essentials like medicines etc, Mobility support through public local rickshaws would be provided for people to be reached to the nearest health centre during emergency and for health check ups, health check would be done at the health centre for tracing where in currently the community is able to have access basic health facilities before reaching out to the district facility. This health centre would be serve as a primary first level tracing centre for basic illness, the medical equipments would enhance the quality of support, awareness programs through IEC material would also be done in various villages as per the operational plan of the project implementation team.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1500 Families would have food security during this time of unemployment and loss of livelihood.
The health equipment would support the health centres to have effective mechanism for tracing and treating vulnerable sick people.
The transportation support would assist people 200 sick individuals to have accessibility to health centres for all medical emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
